        "title": "fix: sanitize Google thinking payloads for Vertex",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Extends the Google thinking payload sanitizer to `google-vertex` and `google-gemini-cli` APIs in addition to `google-generative-ai`.\n- Preserves passthrough behavior for non-Google APIs.\n- Adds focused SDK stream-wrapper coverage for the new API identifiers.\n\nCloses #38327.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/google-stream-wrappers.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/extra-params.google.test.ts extensions/google/provider-models.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-stream.test.ts`\n- `codex review --uncommitted`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Google Vertex and Gemini CLI streaming payloads now receive the same thinking-config sanitization as Google Generative AI payloads.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL-native checkout at `origin/main` `b86435f0b5`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran format, `git diff --check`, focused Google/plugin-sdk Vitest, then `codex review --uncommitted` in `/root/openclaw-wsl-google-38327`.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused Vitest passed 5 files / 47 tests; Codex review reported no actionable regression.\n\nObserved result after fix: `google-generative-ai`, `google-vertex`, and `google-gemini-cli` payloads convert invalid thinking budget payloads to the expected thinking level; non-Google APIs keep the original payload unchanged.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full CI was not run locally; this was scoped to the affected Google stream-wrapper and related Google model tests.\n",
